verbose_text: Another rodent study found oxytocin influenced behavior such that maternal rats that exhibited high levels of Licking, Grooming and Arch Backed Nursing behaviors (LG-ABN) had higher oxytocin receptor densities in brain structures associated with oxytocin release as compared to maternal rats with low LG-ABN levels [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
